usefull on the big &quot;Uber Raids&quot;, and the Barrier of Force is much more usefull on a raid then a nuke, same goes for the cleric staff realy. Sure, it's nice to have when out exping but it is not a major thing, just saves a little bit of mana. But on a raid situation, the effect on the cleric mace is simply amazing and cuts down recovery time increadbly.<br>
<br>
Then there is the wiz staff, eh .. it's so-so for exping not really &quot;required&quot; material, but it's a great effect for a wizard who goes raiding alot vs monsters that have strong AOE attacks. Now given, the resists on this staff could be improved a bit, but the thing is - if you dont like the resits for raids, use the effect then slap on a better hand held resist item. Not that big of a hassle.<br>
<br>
If these epics are supposed to be the &quot;be all and end all&quot; of class defining items, then these quests are to damn easy. I can think of a few harder things out there then killing Jumpalot, Cazic, VS and Phin.<br>
<br>
If these were ment to be trueley uber-epic items IMO, they should require atleast 1 piece each from the hardest monsters/zones in the game (top levels of sky, veeshans peak, Trakanon, Fear, Hate).<br>
<br>
The effect on the weapon itself is very usefull for a raiding wizard, and for daily exping wise, it complements the solists robe of invocation nicely, and the fact that it works good with the manaskin is a nice boon. Do you need a rend robe or a mana robe to make this staff worth having? no, the fact is - If you go on raids alot where monsters whack out high damage aoes. Barrier of Force is a usefull effect.<br>
